main event: An observation of a possible satellite near Pearl Harbor, Hawaii, was reported on May 7, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed for 7 minutes and was noted to be as bright as the brightest planet., The observation was made under slight overcast conditions., The object was reported to be moving very fast across the sky., The object was seen moving in a course towards the east., No specific satellite identification could be confirmed, but it was suggested it could be a Pegasus or other visible satellites.
